Recipe - I always love White Sugar Cake for it's honeycomb chewy texture ğŸ, how delicious it is and it's light yeasty aroma from the fermentation process ğŸ˜‹. Plus it's not difficult at all (though as the name suggests, it uses a bit of white sugar so eat in moderation)! ğŸ˜¬ This is a simple yet satistifying traditional Chinese steamed cake, and is most often enjoyed as a tea or breakfast item ğŸ«–, so you can find these in tea houses or even by traditional kueh shops, hawkers in Singapore and Malaysia, super nostalgic!  Recipe (Cup measurements in blog, more recipes in profile!) - Sugar syrup: 3 pandan leaves, 200ml water, 120g sugar - Main batter - 200ml water, 155g rice flour - 4g instant yeast - 4g baking powder - Vegetable oil (for oiling of cake pan)  Steps 1. Prepare sugar syrup - At low heat, heat up pandan leaves, water and sugar until all sugar has dissolved 2. Main batter - In a separate large bowl, whisk water and rice flour until smooth 3. Whisk in sugar water solution (do not add pandan in). Then, leave mixture to cool till lukewarm 4. Whisk in instant yeast, followed by baking powder 5. Cover with plastic wrap / cloth (leaving a small hole), and ferment until bubbly, approx 2.5 hours 6. Oil 7 inch round pan, then give the batter a gentle stir before pouring in 7. Steam at high heat for approx 22 - 28 minutes. Then, leave to cool for at least 10 mins before serving. I like to use a plastic knife or well oiled knife to make clean cuts 8. Serve and enjoy! #easyrecipe #easyrecipes #homecafe #kuih #chinesefood #southeastasia #ricecake #localfood #recipeideas #recipeidea

My tips for making the fluffiest and nicely textured marble cake is to use ingredients at  room temperature and to take your time to incorporate the ingredients (apart from the flour, which you shouldnâ€™t overmix!) ğŸ˜‹ doing so will allow you to achieve the best of both worlds - fluffy and moist â˜ï¸ Do you like marble cakes too ğŸ™†ğŸ»â€â™‚ï¸? Ingredients 225g butter, softened 145 granulated white sugar 3 eggs (room temp) 90ml milk (room temp) 10ml vanilla 210g flour 4g baking powder 18g cocoa powder Steps 1. Cream together the butter and sugar for a couple of minutes until light and fluffy 2. Whisk in the 3 eggs one at a time (different from video!), followed by milk and vanilla 3. Whisk in the flour and baking powder until well incorporated. Divide the batter into two, and whisk in the cocoa powder for one of it 4. Alternate vanilla and chocolate batter to do marbling. Use a knife to cut through gently to create swirls! 5. Bake 160C in 7 or 8 in round tin for 52-55 mins till golden brown. 8 in square works too - bigger tin will have slightly shorter cakes but less cracks 6. Naeema choked ğŸ˜” It happened in a split second despite making sure that our living room was clean and nothing small was on the floor. Inaaya was doing her art and craft on the table..one of her decorative small item dropped onto the floor and we missed the moment when Naeema inserted the item into her mouth. U can find the video in my Ig Stories. I strongly recommend EVERYONE who is watching to get that choking tool for your family and have it at home. I got it from a sponsored ad I saw on IG and I swear, Im glad i purchased itğŸ¥¹ All praises to Allah SWT, he moved my heart to purchase it maybe because to prep me for this day to come. I am still traumatised, together with my helpers as we were all there witnessing her turn blue. My heart was pounding, my hands was trembling while putting the tool together but my mouth uttered " Ok Naeema sayang its ok we gona get this, its ok sayang its ok"  Trust me, at that point I was not sure if it will be ok. But I leave it to Allah and Alhamdullilah he helped us. He also kept me calm and collected during that moment.ğŸ¥¹ After the item got out, I was traumatised and very very relieved- I hugged her so tight and broke down. Called my family right away to inform them as well. â¤ï¸  Disclaimer: NAEEMA WAS NOT LEFT UNATTENDED. Unfortunately, when it happened my helper was feeding ezhaan while keeping her eyes on Naeema. I guess it all had to happen as a reminder for myself and Bilal.  Please send/share this video to all your people and I hope this will create awareness and also to prepare us incase any unwanted emergency were to happen.  #chokingvictim #chokingdevice #chokingdevicesaveslives #naeemabilaljeanpierre #chokingawareness
